		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Megan McNamer</span></strong> prepared for a career in writing by studying ethnomusicology. &ldquo;I like to write about geographies of ambivalence,&rdquo; she says: &ldquo;the liminal, in-between places where travelers meet their destinations.&rdquo; Her essays have appeared in several anthologies and a variety of magazines, including <em>Salon</em> and <em>Sports Illustrated</em>. She lives in Missoula, Montana, and is currently at work on a book of essays.</p><a href="/contributors/megan-mcnamer" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
